-- Zloty Advances to Snap Three-Day Retreat on Improving U.S. Data
-- B y   P i o t r   S k o l i m o w s k i
-- 2012-03-15T15:16:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-15/zloty-advances-to-snap-three-day-retreat-on-improving-u-s-data.html
The Polish zloty advanced for the
first time in four days after reports showed New York-area
manufacturing grew and fewer Americans filed jobless claims in a
sign the global economy is improving.  The zloty appreciated 0.8 percent to 4.1277 per euro as of
4 p.m. in Warsaw. It was the third-steepest gain among 25
emerging-market currencies tracked by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Skolimowski in Warsaw at 
 pskolimowski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
